For the record, we’re just getting started. 😉

My calendar is open for podcast coaching clients who are ready to grow an engaged audience, crush their income goals and realize the true potential of being a podcaster 😘

The one skill that has been totally worth learning has been pitching.

Pitching is simply asking for what you want.

Whether you want to be a guest on more shows, want to work with brands or speak on stages, pitching can help you get there. 

Struggling with what to say or how to say it, let’s chat 1:1 podcast coaching.

Did you hear about this @ihgonerewards bonus! It’s expiring tonight so make sure you download the app and log in before midnight to claim your 1,000 points bonus.

For more financially savvy travel tips follow The Thought Card Podcast and me of course ☺️.

🤔 Want to work with more brands in 2023? 

Here’s the inside scoop of what brands (really) care about when working with podcasters. 

1. Your reach — how many people listen to your show? 

2. Who do you serve? 

What types of people make up your audience? 

3. How have you worked with other brands? 

Need help navigating the complexities of working with brands? 

Hi, I’m Danielle 👋🏾, a podcast marketing coach passionate about helping indie podcasters make a full-time income by strategically growing their shows and making more money.

To join my 1:1 podcast marketing coaching program DM me for more info or access the application link in my bio.

2022 was one for the books. 🙌🏾

Celebrating 1 full year of entrepreneurship was unreal.

I learned a lot. 

I made mistakes and took calculated risks. 

Now time to rest, daydream about what I’d like 2023 to look like, and spend lots of quality time with my family. 

What are you prioritizing this month?

Everything you create for your show has a purpose and can help grow your show. 📈

Podcast episode descriptions are found within podcast players like Apple Podcasts and Spotify (which have their own search engines) while show notes are found on your website. 

Show notes or “blog posts” have the potential to get picked up by Google.

People searching using different key terms will click on the article and potentially listen to the episode. 

Potentially hundreds and thousands of people will discover your site and podcast every month. 

Either way they’ve now found you without you doing much work outside of optimizing your show notes for search. 

Search engine optimization is powerful for podcasters but we don’t always think about this when we are in creation mode.

Like and follow for more helpful podcast marketing and monetization tips. 

Signing off, your Podcast Marketing Coach 👋🏾

I kept things super simple this year focusing my time and energy on earning more income as a travel podcaster and growing my podcast coaching program. 

I’m really proud of myself and can’t wait to get started on 2023 my goals.

Whether you decide to publish new content or republish older episodes, I say go for. 

A lot of podcasters take a break during the holidays so if you have the bandwidth and capacity, why not take this opportunity to stand out? 

Have you decided to rest or go full steam ahead during the holiday season? 

Oh BTW! If you enjoy my podcasting content, join me over on TikTok!

Someone had to say it. 🤷🏾‍♀️

Posting on social typically reminds your existing audience of new episodes they may want to listen to but it typically doesn’t help get your show in front of new listeners who never heard of you before (unless you’re posting IG Reels or on TikTok). 

If posting on social hasn’t helped much with growing your listenership, you’re not alone. 

Use social to connect, engage and nurture your existing audience on whatever platform you’re on. Be social and have fun. 

To grow your show, focus on discoverability in 2023.

Between my workshops and coaching, DM me for ways we can work together to achieve your podcast growth goals this year.

A friendly reminder to all my podcasters out there. Follow up on those podcast guest appearance pitches and pitches to brands you want to work with. Maybe the last time you reached out wasn’t a good time. Start the new year off strong by following up with all your old leads.

Over the last (4) years I’ve pursued several types of income streams like paid memberships, workshops, digital products and a handful of others. But it wasn’t until I pursued affiliate marketing as passive income and sponsorships as active that I really started to see progress.

Podcast monetization takes experimenting, figuring out what feels good for you and what you find success in. 

If either affiliate marketing or sponsorships is on your list for this year, let’s chat podcast coaching.

I’ve see all different types of podcasts receive funding from horror movies to news, business and travel. 

Podcasts regardless of niche or topic can get funded. What matters most is that your show is aligned with the funder and the grant’s objective. 

So keep applying and don’t forget that my biweekly newsletter will shave hours of research. 

Visit grantsforcreators.com or the link in my bio for more resources.

Who said life stops after having a child? 

Truth is, things are just getting started for world travelers.

A lot of people have reservations about traveling with small kids, and while I get the concerns, I believe now is the best time to explore, especially when looking at the financials. 

Firstly, kids fly free until 2 years old and under 3 get to go to Disney for free and even some cruises. 

Also, many museums, attractions and sites are free for small children. 

For financially savvy travelers there are incredible savings when exploring with your little ones. So, why wait?! 

Plus, I love seeing the world through Baby K’s brown eyes and having many firsts together like our first beach day. Toes in the sand and all 💕.

Should you wait to go to Disney when your kids can actually remember the experience? 

It’s funny how viewpoints change when you start a family. 🤭

Seeing Baby K’s little face watching Beauty and the Beast, meeting Mickey briefly and even feasting on all the delicious food from all around the world made our experience truly unforgettable. 

If you’re wondering if Disney is worth it with a baby, the answer is “YES!” for us at least. 😉

For more of my thoughts (and cost breakdown) stay tuned for a Disney with babies recap episode coming to The Thought Card Podcast very soon!
Cherishing all our firsts together. 💕🐡

Babies have incredible timing. 🤭

There was no way Baby K was going to miss the show. 

While he slept peacefully throughout all the fireworks, he woke up naturally on his own. It’s like he knew doing that would make mommy and daddy over the moon with joy. 💕

Phew! Where do we even begin? 😮‍💨 

With our first cross-country family road trip out of the way: let’s just say we learned A LOT. 

Lol 😂 🫢

Did Baby K manage not to scream or throw a fit during the road trip? 

How much did we spend on gas? Tolls? 

How long did it take us to get to Florida?

Will we ever do this kind of road trip again? 

We’re going to talk about all of this next, so… 

Be sure to follow to get the full scoop on our family travel adventures✌🏾

Celebrating Mother’s Day 💐. 

Life looks incredibly different now as a mama bear but gosh it feels so full with you in it, Baby K. You are my sunshine ☀️.

Hey, I know it’s easy to say we’ll go on a vacation next year when they get a little older but don’t miss out on the opportunity to create memories together, especially when there are so many incredible destinations so close, right in your backyard. 

Go for a hike, stroll around the River Walk, eat ice cream, or spend the afternoon at a new-to-you museum or exhibition at an art gallery. 

Travel with your baby. Seek out experiences to enjoy with your baby. 

They will never be this little again, so enjoy every moment. ❤️❤️❤️

Plus look how gorgeous @hildenethelincolnfamilyhome is in @manchestervermont. 📸

Did you know that you can visit the Lincoln family home in @manchestervermont. 

At the 412-acres “summer cottage”  @hildenethelincolnfamilyhome trace the footsteps of President Abraham Lincoln’s son, Robert Lincoln and his descendants.

See how their family lived (pretty lavish for their time), explore their estate and their Georgian Revival mansion built in 1905. 

My personal favorite, the Formal Garden which has more than one thousand peony blossoms and sprawling mountain views. 🌺

If you love history and want to walk back in time, Hildene takes the prize.

#manchestervermont #vermont #vermontlife #vermontliving

🚙 Driving up the longest paved toll road in America. 

We all know hiking up to the top of the summit but driving offered a whole new experience, perspective, and plenty of thrilling moments. 

The views @mtequinoxskylinedrive_vt were magnifique! 

Mount Equinox Summit stands at 3,848 feet tall and you see towns like @bennington_vermont @helloburlington off in the distance as well as @iloveny and @visitnewhampshirewhitemountain @visitnewhampshire. 

Another must-do while visiting @manchestervermont! 

Don’t forget to take plenty of breaks on your ride down, stopping at all the viewpoints because the drive down is (very) steep so give your brakes a break. 😉

Can you imagine what the Fall foliage looks like?!🍁🍂

#manchestervt #manchestervermont #mountequinox #vermont #vermontlife #ilovermont #visitnew_england #visitnewengland

Everything we could ask for on a relaxing getaway in @manchestervermont started right here at @seesawslodge.

Gorgeous views of the mountains from our balcony, an outdoor hot tub for soaking after a long day of exploring, an on-site historic restaurant and bar, an in-suite tub for soapy baths and plenty of outdoor seating.

This was our first time staying at a lodge with shared living spaces and I absolutely loved it! 

Everyone was so respectful and kind and I can imagine in the winter time how much fun it is to meet other travelers here during ski season.🎿

For more things to do in Manchester, check out my recent posts, reels, and stories in my highlights. 

#manchestervt #manchestervermont #lodge #luxurylodging #vermont #vermonting

I was so anxious about our first flight, which so happened to be a 7.5 hour international flight. 😬😬😬

The good news: we survived and although there were a couple of meltdowns and lots of jumping up and down, everything went smoothly.

A few tips for flying with an infant:

✅ Get to your boarding gate early so you can be one of the first people to board the plane. 

Everything takes longer with a baby, so the few extra minutes to get settled before everyone else is very helpful.

✅ Window seat is preferred so your baby has a little more space, entertainment by looking out the window, and a place to lean on when they fall asleep. 

✨Bonus Tip ✨

✅ Pack an extra set of clothes because you don’t want to be caught in the middle of a blowout when boarding, which happened to us.

✨Toddler Edition ✨ Save for later. 📂

How to spend a day at @theadkx with your baby. 

Grab a 🗺️ at the registeration desk and pick your first stop. 

We recommend starting at ‘Life in the Adirondacks’ exhibit for an overview of how people live, play, and worked in the Adirondacks over the centuries.

Keep an eye out for the play areas where the kids can create their own log houses or pretend to fry 🎣 at a camp. 

Next, time for some outdoor fun: enjoy the swing set with a view then head to the Kid’s Cabin to explore a kid-sized cabin fully equipped with a play kitchen. 

Hungry? Grab lunch at Lake View Cafe. 🍽️

Baby K loved the Grilled Cheese Sandwiches 🧀 

While you’re there, snap family photos of the glistening Blue Mountain Lake 📸

With full bellies, drop off your stroller at the front desk and go on a 3/4 mile nature walk on Minnow Pond Trail. 

There’s so much to see here, so expect to take frequent stops and if needed there are benches to sit along the way. 

Follow the orange trail markers for the easier route. Spend some time at the boat house before hiking back up to the main campus. 

Last stop, the new art exhibit, ‘Artists & Inspiration in the Wild’ an art gallery illustrating how the Adirondacks sparks creativity. 

There are over 250 pieces of art to marvel at from landscape paintings to handwoven baskets.

By now your little one is tired and deserving of a sweet treat, so go grab ice cream at @custardslaststand1958. 

Save this post for your next Adirondack vacation exploring Upstate New York. 

#YesNY #iSpyNY #adirondackexperience

A mini @visitclarksvilletn itinerary for history lovers! 😍

📁 Save this post for a fun day of exploration. 

🔦 @dunbarcavestatepark - Take a guided tour with a park ranger to learn about how this prehistoric cave has been used for thousands of years. 

You’ll see hand drawn images and carvings from the Mississippians dating back to the 14th-century. 

🌽 @historiccollinsvilletn to learn about rural Tennessee life from 1830 to 1900. 

There are 16 authentic buildings on the 40-acre settlement from a Blacksmith shop to a one-room schoolhouse and church.

🖼️ Visit @customshousemuseum to learn about the influential people who shaped Clarksville. 

As the second largest general interest museum in Tennessee, there’s so much to see here, including an art gallery, one of the largest train model layouts in the southeast, an entire floor for kids, and more!

It was such an honor to coach a room full of podcasters on how best to position themselves for sponsorships and brand partnerships @afrosandaudio! 

I know so many podcasters who don’t consider sponsorships as a viable income stream because they feel like their audience is too small or they don’t know where to start. 

Looking beyond the downloads, here are some key insights from my session. 

1. Focus on building your portfolio so you can show and tell brand partners how you can help them reach their goals.

Paint the picture of what it could be like working with you with a variety of examples. 

This is also great practice for you to get really good at creating all different types of content and know which ones work best for you. 

2. Podcast sponsorships is very much about building relationships. Don’t fall into the transactional trap. Remember there are real people behind brands. 

3. Create win-win-win campaigns where all parties involved are satisfied;
(You, the client (the brand) and your listeners).

Hi, 👋🏾 I’m Danielle, a podcast marketing coach and a travel podcaster. 

I love helping podcasters better position themselves to get the most out of their shows whether to build authority, grow an engaged audience or monetize. 

Follow for podcasting insights, tips, and inspiration.

🚀 Not taking a break this summer meant I had fresh content waiting for my listeners on road trips and summer break. I’m a travel podcaster, summer is my time to shine! 

🚀 I doubled down on writing articles on my website that supported my podcast as a whole vs only promoting one episode. 

🚀 I was way more consistent with emailing my newsletter: probably the best job I’ve done in years. 

Growing a podcast audience sometimes feels like playing chess. Don’t forget I packaged some of my best templates, checklists and workflows in the 2024 Podcast Planner!
